Working on getting access to Cabilis as a Mith Marr High Elf. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 864<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/8/01 9:38:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Meganerf to the Kael and Skyshrine Armor Quests</span><hr size=1> Not sure on Skyshrine but for Kael armor this isn't really much of a nerf.  The quest givers are on Kromzek faction (stormgiant).  To get to the quest givers you must walk past King Tormax and his court.  Therefor you need at least Dubious faction with Tormax to get to the quest givers.  To get Tormax to dubious you must <br>
   a) hunt enough dwarves/dragons to get Kromzek to apprehensive<br>
   b) turn in approx 60 coldain heads or 200 ice kobald paws to Capt Bvellos giving +kromrif, +kromzek, +KingTormax, -ClawsofVeeshan  and/or kill coldain royals.<br>
 <br>
Old Numeric faction values:<br>
<br>
below -725, ready to attack<br>
 -725 to -500, threatening<br>
 -500 to -100, dubious<br>
 -100 to -1, apprehensive<br>
 0 to 99, indifferent<br>
 100 to 499, amiable<br>
 500 to 699, kindly<br>
 700 and up, warmly<br>
<br>
<br>
By time you get King Tormax to just dubious (where I am now) the Kromzek are already at Warmly.  If you want to do many of the other quests you need to get Tormax to at least Indifferent. Thats another +500 faction swing.  Kromzek are already warmly at dubious.  By doing another 500 points faction with Tormax should push me even higher with Kromzek.  Now to get the armor you have to hunt in ToV.  Well ToV mobs give +kromzek faction pushing you even higher.   I would bet that many people that are now warmly with Kromzek will be Allied when they log on today.<br>
<br>
Also, you can only have a max of a 2000 faction swing.  That is why when you have hunted some zones in mass amounts you stop getting faction hits, you've already gotten 2000 from base.  I started at threatening with giants, one kill to save a friend put me at ready to attack. So therefore I was at -725 or so by default.  That means the most I could get my faction to (and anyone else other than Rallos Zek worshippers who start at dubious) would be +1275.  So I would guess that Allied is now at +1000.  Thats a 300 point increase from warmly compared to a 200 point increase from kindly to warmly.  Not really that big of a deal.  I bet those that are indifferent or better with King Tormax are already there.  Those that are warmly with King Tormax should easily be allied.<br>
<br>
By time most people are able to get to ToV and win armor pieces they should already be close.  Just be glad the quest givers aren't on King Tormax faction anymore like they used to be.<br>
<br>
As for those on dragon faction ... /shrug. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=View&Profile=0&Id=60309">Jaradis Stormcaller</a> - 53rd Mystic - (Kael Faction)<br>
